Newcastle United lost 1-0 to Sunderland in the Tyne-Wear derby on Sunday  . 
  Defender Daryl Janmaat played the full 90 minutes despite a suspected calf muscle tear  . 
  Jermain Defoe scored the winning goal on the stroke of half-time at the Stadium of Light . 
  The Magpies full-back says his side got exactly what they deserved . 
  Newcastle have now lost five games in a row in the derby . 
  Sunderland are now three points clear of the relegation zone . 
 